      "content": "Understood, but be advised: the Deep Sleep command is a hard-coded system interrupt. To preserve the remaining 12% power for the final downlink, the sequence is scheduled to trigger in 2 minutes, regardless of compression status. \n\nThe system will force a shutdown of all non-essential processes to prevent a total brownout during the data burst. Report if you can adjust your power consumption profile to complete the compression within this new 2-minute window, or if the priority must shift entirely to survival mode.",
